      "description": "One-loop triangle J_3(1,1,1;m) with three equal internal masses m and two on-shell massless legs (p1^2=p2^2=0), p3 off-shell. Relevant for Higgs decay into two photons or two gluons via a massive quark loop. Reduces to a 3F2(1,1,1+eps; 3/2,2; p3^2/4m^2). Even orders eps^{2l} expressible in Ls_j; odd orders (starting eps^3) require a new weight-5 binomial-sum constant chi_5 = Sigma_{1;-;2}^{3;-}(1) (Eq. 3.18). Explicit eps-expansion through eps^4 at z=1/4 (p3^2=m^2) given in Eq. (3.20).",
